
[1]insurance

   INSU'RANCE, n. [from insure.] The act of insuring or assuring against
   loss or damage; or a contract by which one engages for a stipulated
   consideration or premium per cent to make up a loss which another may
   sustain. Insurance is usually made on goods or property exposed to
   uncommon hazard, or on lives.

   Insurance company, a company or corporation whose business is to insure
   against loss or damage.
